It‚Äôs always the rich kids with daddy issues and terrible human beings for parents crying about students with bursaries or full loans. Poor students in this country have literally had all resources stripped away from us.
We don‚Äôt have anyone to rely on for rent, travel or buying a laptop/basic uni costs etc. A lot of us contribute to our home households rents/bills too because our parents are either disabled, on benefits and/or in insecure work which has been made extremely worse this year.
The vast majority of us have been ‚Äúscanning barcodes‚Äù (if you‚Äôre lucky) since 16. So instead of attacking & being envious of what little we get maybe you should advocate for the fact that all students in this country get a shit deal & this government doesn‚Äôt value higher education or the concept of universalism.

As a northern lass myself I can tell you that these northerners of which you speak are in fact the minority. Pretty much none of my friends get anywhere near the maximum loan. This is a country wide issue because those in charge of the student loans simply do not make it clear enough that everyone‚Äôs parents are expected to make up the gap. This is not an issue of north vs south, it‚Äôs us all as students vs a system that has upped the fees and lowered the wages. Always remember who the root of the issues are (hint: it‚Äôs not any member of the general population)

This is a country wide issue because those in charge of the student loans simply do not make it clear enough that everyone‚Äôs parents are expected to make up the gap. This is not an issue of north vs south, it‚Äôs us all as students vs a system that has upped the fees and lowered the wages. Always remember who the root of the issues are (hint: it‚Äôs not any member of the general population)

#ConcreteUEAconfessions20663
I surely can‚Äôt be the only one here that is in the same situation.
Because my family come from the south and are educated, they have well paid jobs and they are in the highest band of household income for calculating my maintenance loan. Therefore I get the lowest ¬£4K allowance, whereas some kid from ‚Äúup narth‚Äù with a single mum who has a drug addiction and votes Brexit gets the full ¬£10k per year maintenance loan.
On the face of it you can justify this. By virtue of not being born north of Hampstead, I have been granted more opportunities throughout my childhood. However it does mean there‚Äôs an expectation that families are meant to contribute the deficit between whatever is loaned to us and approximately ¬£10k, in my case ¬£6k.
This would work fine if that actually happened, but in my case it doesn‚Äôt. My parents would rather drive around in their multiple Maseratis, buy custom Cotswold-blue kitchens for their third home and go on ‚Äúart trips‚Äù to galleries in Florence while tasting the difference between the 2016 vintage and 2017 vintage Mo√´t. It seems that because I didn‚Äôt make it to Cambridge, like they did, I don‚Äôt qualify for any help from them.
I‚Äôve spoken to them about this on multiple occasions, they won‚Äôt hear any of it, not even a half-way house. What can I do to make up the financial difference? Is there anything I can do to increase my loan?
I‚Äôm happy to work a little bit to make up the difference, but not to the point where my Northern working-class compatriots around me are swilling around with champagne in helicopters with their newly found so-called ‚Äúwealth‚Äù while I beep barcodes in Tescos for eight quid an hour for all my three years here.

-

Rights so this isnt some where I'd normally put out but it's generally alot easier to take advice or criticism from mostly strangers. Long story but I'll keep it short maybe around 2 years ago my mental health was quite bad, regular self harm and on several occasions what you could call suicide attempts. Obviously with all that going on it put alot of strain on my main friend ships so we gradually drifted apart which I think was the right thing to do because it's not right for my burdens to impact them negatively however do you think it's normal to feel selfish and guilty about the things you've done in the past, like I wish nothing but the best in the future for them but I still think I had negative effects on them via my actions. Although i was acting in a very altered state of mind however and meant no malice atall, instead in my view I tried to not burden them with my issues but of course if difficult when you are so low and do need help. Then the positive effect they had on my life cant be underestimated. So I dont know if these are normal feeling to be experiencing, any advice? One additional point do you think its necessary to announce self harm to someone newish you're talking to or wait till later on to announce it. Sorry for the long post any advice is appreciated

I dont want sympathy, I just want a way to make the hurt and pain go away

On the night of the 5th of July, my friends and I were walking by the lake. Some among our group decided to dip their toes in the lake, I didn‚Äôt partake coz I thought it was a stupid idea also low key scared of water in the night. After getting out we were heading to the ziggurats where I live and stopped and questioned by security, the man was very amicable and I even asked him whether I did something wrong and he replied ‚Äòno‚Äô yet insisted on getting my ID for ‚Äúreference‚Äù purposes. I asked him that I did not want to receive a warning e-mail. However I‚Äôve received a warning e-mail which is not appealable and accuses me of:
General Regulation 10.1.16 You must not commit or participate in any act that constitutes disorderly conduct causing nuisance or distress. and
Regulation 12 (4) (c) It shall be a disciplinary offence for any student to be in or on the Broad except as may be expressly or by implication authorised by the University authorities concerned.
I‚Äôve already received one for breaking quarantine rules on the 3rd of May for having a birthday party for one of my flat mate, even though all the participants were people from my flat, at that time I was accused of:
Regulation 10.1.16 You must not commit or participate in any act that constitutes disorderly conduct causing nuisance or distress.
Regulation 12.1.1 You must take reasonable care for your own safety and for the safety of the University‚Äôs staff, students, officers, visitors and anyone else who may be affected by your acts or omissions.
They‚Äôve put these on my permanent record and I‚Äôm allowed to appeal them. The truth is since the population on campus has thinned out UEA security regularly barge in to our flat every now and then and also have been going through every accommodations multiple times (at least 4) to make sure that people who have left aren‚Äôt actually squatting and that was during the peak of quarantine. Few days ago they woke me up asking me whether there was someone knocking on my window, which is idiotic since I do not live on the ground floor. My question to you folks is whether that is abuse of power? And also I fear that I may receive a silly warning again and that will be my third strike SO what should I do??

Myself and two others, a British friend of mine and an American boy, went into a 24 hour offie to try and get some beer. Locate a crate of 12 beers, ask how much it is, and the bloke says it's ¬£42 (gotta love London). Now at that point, any typical Brit would probably shuffle their feet a bit, nod and mumble a "hmm yeah maybe" before awkwardly buying a Snickers or a bottle of Coke and running out. While my fellow British friend and I did that very little routine, the American boy whips around, looks the shop keeper straight in the eye, and says "are you fucking KIDDING me?". Cue utter mortification from my friend and I, and us hurriedly bustling the American out before he can cause more offence.

Tips on how to be friends with an ex by a girl who is friends with all of her exes, and even set two of them up with other friends:
1. Understand that you're under no obligation to stay friends. Be sure that it's what you want
2. Take some time after the break up to heal and recover. Don't talk for 2-3 weeks, just to get over the initial pain. Make sure that when you come back, being friends is what you both want
3. Make sure you're not staying friends with them just in the hopes you'll get back together. This can turn toxic and usually ends in tears
4. Don't view them as 'your ex that you're friends with'. If you do, the fact you have a history will always taint your friendship. They should be your friend first and foremost, and the fact you dated should be something laughed and jokes about
Disclaimer: this only works if you're both committed to making it work. Friendships are just like relationships, they require teamwork

text:
#ConcreteUEAconfessions20318
Ok I‚Äôm gonna go off here.
I am a doctor, one of the brand new stepped-up-as-a-med-student cohort. I have tried to make sure I stand up for all of my colleagues in health and care during this pandemic but now it‚Äôs time for you to stand up for all of us.
In their infinite wisdom, HMRC have decided that a Covid test - if taken by an employee for an employer - is a ‚Äòbenefit in kind‚Äô and thus taxable. Like a company car, or private medical insurance through your work. So that means that someone is going to put a value on a Covid test, and then tax you on that value.
Even if you‚Äôve tested negative, can you imagine seeing that little deduction on your payslip? And if you‚Äôve tested positive, how galling is it to pay for the privilege of not being able to work, all while knowing that you‚Äôre suffering from a new disease which has killed hundreds of thousands of people across the world?
I‚Äôve been lucky, I‚Äôve had one test (negative) and one antibody test (also negative), both through work. But I have no idea if those tests are going to show up on my next payslip and, if they do, how much I‚Äôll be paying. Ok, I‚Äôm a doctor, we‚Äôre famously well-paid (ahem ¬£13.54/h according to my June payslip - not to be sniffed at, certainly, but not exactly the Mo√´t Medic lifestyle it‚Äôs portrayed to be), I can take a hit. But what about the nurses (¬£12.74/h, according to a quick google), healthcare assistants (¬£9.21), phlebotomists (¬£10.09), ambulance technicians (¬£11.20)? What about the porters, the care workers, the till assistants, the breakdown call centre staff? They‚Äôre all Key Workers too and you can be damn sure they‚Äôll be on minimum wage or close to it.
Now imagine you‚Äôre in an industry which requires regular tests. Yeah.
Chancellor Rishi Sunak says that he is ‚Äòurgently investigating‚Äô this, but how much can we believe the party who scrapped nurses‚Äô bursaries, demanded students worked on the front line during the pandemic and then tried to not pay them?
We are two days past the celebration of the NHS‚Äôs 72nd birthday. Two days and seventy-two years since Nye Bevan established that ‚Äúillness is not an indulgence for which people have to pay ... nor an offence for which they should be penalised‚Äù. However, our government seem hell-bent on doing both, and shafting the people who keep us well and safe at the same time.
If you still think that Johnson, Cummings, Patel et al are handling this pandemic well, then I just don‚Äôt know what else to say to you.

Recently theres been the odd one where people have submitted "cheaters" initialls which I dont think is morally right to publically expose someone here, especially with no way to validate the claim, people sharing initials and cancel culture being as it is atm. I have been working in pubs since I was 16 and the first pub I worked in was a bit of a shocker in terms of the management. While it had alright beer, nice food and an overall good reputation the management was terrible. The boss has the personality of a wet mop and his wife, who had no clue, clearly wore the trousers. Long story short I did not like his wife at all I found her lazy, incompetent and snobbish. Both of them were like this really, and having worked in far better establishments since I have come to realize how bad this place was.
Anyway, this one time as a rare kind of 'thank you' thing from my boss, he threw a curry night lock in with free drinks and all. It was a very generous gesture for sure, but his wife was getting absolutely shitfaced and so I thought I would too. 6-7 pints in and I'm pretty far gone (I was 17 at this point) and so was she. With all my pent up hatred towards her and the mixture of alcohol I ended up laying into her - calling her a c*nt to her face and calling out all the stuff she does (or doesn't do). Everyone there, including her husband thought it was hilarious.
Around an hour later I ended up throwing up all over the toilets - she cleaned it up, somehow I didn't get fired and rocked up 6 hours later for my 12 hour shift with a massive hangover.

I listed them off and then it clicked: I was forgetting the gin because I was thinking about all the numerous non-alcoholic components! No customers had noticed and said anything! Yet another American story here!
So, in my first year of sixth form, we had an American student join us since she‚Äôd moved to Norwich from Florida.
Anyway, over the first few weeks, she had started to get friendly with our group and asked what ‚Äòwanker‚Äô meant as she‚Äôd heard us use it few times in our conversations. We explained and then she came out with some absolute gold!
She explained that her music teacher was called ‚ÄòMr Wanker‚Äô and to top it off, she provided proof from her year book! (See photo below).
Oh and one last anecdote from the same American:
She was in my chemistry class for our A-Levels and one time in chemistry she was asked what hard water meant...her response: ‚Äúisn‚Äôt hard water just ice?‚Äù....bruh.
This kinda shit went on for years, we‚Äôre still good friends with her even though she is a mess!

Not at all a confession but a thank you.
As an international exchange student that was supposed to be here all semester, I‚Äôm heartbroken that I have to leave this fantastic place so soon. Everyone I‚Äôve met at the this (both residents and internationals) have been so welcoming and kind. I‚Äôm so sad that I have to leave but I wanted to let you all know how happy I was to study here for this short time, and how lucky you guys are to have such a fantastic school. I know you take Uni for granted, I definitely do often, but if you take a step back, this school and little town is extraordinary.
Thank you Norwich, I‚Äôll be back to visit someday.

Hi everyone, I'm here representing Take Five UEA, we are a mental health initiative that helps students with their mental wellbeing.
Sadly, we have had to cancel our in-person sessions. We have moved everything online though, we have a Discord Server which you can join (message me or comment for the link) and we will run 3 sessions a week on Monday, Wednesday and Friday.
Here is an article to try and help you look after your wellbeing during the potential self-isolation period.
https://www.mind.org.uk/information-support/coronavirus-and-your-wellbeing/
Above all else, don't panic, wash your hands and look after yourselves. We are here for you and will help you with whatever we can. <3

text:
#ConcreteUEAconfessions15852
Kobe was an icon of mine as I'm sure he was for many of you. Life is truly unpredictable and unfortunately we never what breath will be our last and so I want to use this moment while I'm in my bed in tears to encourage you all...
Treasure those closest to you, friends and family alike hold them dear, make each moment precious. Set aside past wrongdoings and as much as you can live in peace with everyone make that effort today to forgive before the chance passes you by. Tell that person how you really feel because what's the point in holding it in when we are not guaranteed tommorow?
Lastly live everyday to the fullest and as much as you can be happy.
Rest in power and paradise to the Black Mamba, you will be missed üíúüíõüíúüíõüíúüíõ

Please no Hate, this is just what I have seen!
Hope everyone is getting on alright with this last part of the semester, as a second year it's been going alright with me so far. But in all seriousness I do hope next semester goes better for a lot of you. I dont plan on having this be my last meme of 2019 as its tragic as heck! But needed to sort of evaluate all I have seen with these posts. Next memes I post will be comedic gold - trust me.
All in all, one last push until this semester ends, so try as hard as you can and try to the best of your abilities!
- EURO
p.s. apologies If this post has offended you. I haven't ever used a warning like this before, but to be safe I'm adding this in. This meme ain't targeted towards anyone at all, this is merely a a populated collection of topics I have seen during this semester at UEA.

text: When the SU finally confirm PMB is cancelled.
post_text: When the SU finally confirm PMB is cancelled.

text:
SU: Hey, we're cancelling PMB. Here's a vague statement where we say it's too unsafe for us to hold (but don't offer anything in the way of what was unsafe, what the issues are or why weren't able to fix them). We're going to sort of say we'll do something instead but not really give any details because we haven't got any ideas yet. Sorry, we forgot to mention any of this during the elections btw.
Students:
Note: I know people will comment and say that the SU does a lot more than PMB and they do undoubtedly do some good work. But at the end of the day, they've had a whole year to sort out these issues, put out a really badly worded statement and are accountable to the students they represent and help fund them. The two things the majority of students want to SU to get right is the LCR and PMB, and they've sadly failed with both of these.

Well you guys seem mad keen for this to happen, which we love! So here's the plan, if PMB is canceled we assemble in earlham park (by that cafe thing?) at 12:00 on Sat 11th of May for a big old party in tha park, we'll bring the sound, we need you to bring the numbers & the good vibes ‚ù§

text:
If you guys are annoyed/sad about PMB being cancelled, the SSS (or lack of), the lack of communication or anything then DO SOMETHING! Start a petition, write an open letter, plan a rally or protest, email/call the SU. Nothing will change by only posting on concrete confessions. If you think 3rd years should be given priority for tickets or the SU needs to do better email them and give them suggestions, or talk to a rep for your course/school. The SU can always improve and aren't always 100% the best, but they don't want us to be unhappy and they want to hear our opinions. On the SU website it legit says to contact them (see attached picture) and you can vote and add ideas!! THINGS CAN CHANGE AND WE CAN CHANGE THEM.
SU Tel: 01603 593272
SU E-mail: union.info@uea.ac.uk
post_text:
If you guys are annoyed/sad about PMB being cancelled, the SSS (or lack of), the lack of communication or anything then DO SOMETHING! Start a petition, write an open letter, plan a rally or protest, email/call the SU. Nothing will change by only posting on concrete confessions. If you think 3rd years should be given priority for tickets or the SU needs to do better email them and give them suggestions, or talk to a rep for your course/school. The SU can always improve and aren't always 100% the best, but they don't want us to be unhappy and they want to hear our opinions. On the SU website it legit says to contact them (see attached picture) and you can vote and add ideas!! THINGS CAN CHANGE AND WE CAN CHANGE THEM.
SU Tel: 01603 593272
SU E-mail: union.info@uea.ac.uk

text: I'm spending the summer alone in Norwich and regretting it. In the space of a few weeks I've become more and more reclusive and paranoid to the point where I'm eating ginger cake in a santa costume and chugging down my own shitily made bootleg snakebites. I keep refreshing my emails but still nothing, I try to read but I can't... All i can seem to do is sprawl across the couch and watch doomsday preppers, because everything else is already watched. I feel so alone and I'm losing my mind here. I need people. When are people coming back? I need work. When are reading lists out out? I need sticky floors. When is Brandon Flowers coming out of his cage?

In this society, we study Internet cultural, we probably end up running talks and produce report on historic and current Internet phenomenon. The idea is to investigate why certain ideas/memes spread, why some of them don't, and how to create new ideas/memes that spread. My idea for this society is to make the fun side of the Internet intellectual. It is a bit like knowyourmeme.com, but more academically oriented. text:
It is not wrong to enquiry about a refund for lectures missed due to strikes.
It is not wrong to complain about how annoying it is to have to commute just to find out the lectures are cancelled.
We pay for this education and we expect to get the education we pay for. Student loan or not doesn‚Äôt change the fact we pay it. So saying we will never see it doesn‚Äôt matter because some people pay it direct and for some people it is the principle of the thing.
It is not wrong to ask the university for a refund. Why? Because it makes the strike more chaotic for the university which makes the strike more effective. It doesn‚Äôt undermine the strike.
So, strike supporter or not, don‚Äôt feel bad about asking for a refund because it is your consumer rights to do so.

text:
Does anyone have calcium hydroxide?
I found an unused gas cartridge near where I live about a week or two ago. Today, I found an empty/used one at the same spot again. So my question is, what's inside that cartridge? This kind of cartridge is commonly used to store nitrous oxide or carbon dioxide. Nitrous oxide cartridge is commonly used as a whipping agent for whipped cream, because nitrous oxide is soluble in fat. Carbon dioxide cartridge is commonly used by cyclists who have too much money.
I have a suspicion that this cartridge contains nitrous oxide, because nitrous oxide has euphoriant effects if inhaled. I have a feeling that people who live near me have been committing substance abuse. This is because it is unlikely that the same (group of) cyclist(s) would get tyre puncture at the same spot within a 2 week span and end up using carbon dioxide cartridge in both occasions. Carbon dioxide cartridge is not exactly cheap.
If the cartridge contains carbon dioxide, upon discharge into calcium hydroxide solution, the solution would turn cloudy due to the formation of calcium carbonate. The balanced equation is as follows:
Ca(OH)2 + CO2 = CaCO3 + H2O

text:
Went to sit in Cafe 57 in JSC and said to myself, 'I remember when I came in here to read Mary Barton two years ago...'
Then it hit me.
TWO.
YEARS.
AGO.
HEEEEEEEEEELLLLLLLLLLLLLLLPPPPPPPPPPPPPP!!!!!!!!!!!!
Where the fuck did it go?
Time STOP! Pleasssseeee!!!!!
(btw I think the reason you freshers get it so bad is because some of us secretly want to be in a similar position to you. 2nd years are having to cope with things actually counting towards their degree, and 3rd years are having to cope with the impending fear of graduation. You, on the other hand, have just started, and yes things don't count, but they may still feel like they do, as you feel like they'll tell you how good you'll be at writing real essays soon -- which btw, you shouldn't have to worry about, as your essay writing WILL improve, and IS improving, even if you feel like it isn't -- and you have your own fears, quite rightfully. So if anyone comes up to you and belittles you for being a 'fresher', think, 'NYA NYA I'M IN FIRST YEAR AND YOU'RE NOT! FEELS GOOD TO BE ME!)
Now if you'll excuse me, I'm going to go find my original copy of Mary Barton, sit in Cafe 57, and wish the exact spot I'm in to go back exactly 730 days...

text: I just finished watching an overwhelming and tragic BBC documentary about students taking their own lives. My immediate reaction was to submit this message, hopefully transcending the ‚Äòclich√©s‚Äô of ‚Äòyou are not alone‚Äô and ‚Äòit‚Äôs okay to not be okay.‚Äô - Those messages don‚Äôt exist solely for campaigning, they exist because they are completely true. I almost dropped out during my first year at UEA, and in my second year I‚Äôm still struggling to find the help I want and need. I‚Äôve seen multiple posts on this page concerning mental health and poor counselling options, and because of this I understand why depression can feel like a path leading nowhere, but it needs to be said: you are alive and special and loved and you make mistakes but don‚Äôt we all? Be a badass, be strong, for every bad thing there is something so much better. I‚Äôd like to make this post a positive thread, one that inspires dumb laughter. So, comment crazy, happy things. I‚Äôll start: I think pinecones are rad, my dog is the cutest (although yours may be too), I have multiple countries to visit, I‚Äôve ripped too many shirts on nights out, leftover Yorkshire puddings with whipped cream and honey are wicked...

text:
This conflict between residents of Hickling/Barton and the rest of the university is frankly absurd. We ALL got into this university due to the fact that we ALL worked hard for it. I for one as a Hickling resident, and I also speak for many others in my flat, do not come from a rich family. I will leave here with the same debt and job prospects as the rest of all of my fellow students, and that's all that counts. Whoever made the comment about working hard for money clearly doesn't understand how the world works as the majority of my friends are scraping the barrel when they work insane hours AND have university degrees. This university though is a new environment for all of us, where our backgrounds don't matter but our academic ability AND work ethic does. Why should the place we sleep at night in order to get up and work all day drive a rift in this academic-socialist bubble we live in, protected from the rest of the world (I am by no means an advocate of socialism it is just a technical term)?
Yours,
A concerned non-fuck-boy History student

text:
I broke up with my gf before coming to Uni (Not because of long distance, she lives a while away anyway), but we decided to remain friends.
We met up again and I could clearly tell she still had feelings for me. I did too, so I started making out with her and it led to us casually hooking up when we met up.
We made it clear that we're not in a relationship and were just friends that did stuff and had no obligation to be loyal to one another, but neither of us really want to be with anyone else emotionally.
My mates got in my head and now I'm worried that if we keep going like this one or both of us is going to get hurt.
I still really care for her, but also want to experience uni life as it were, but I'm scared if I keep this up I'll either lose her or miss out on student life, but also if I end it I'll make things weird and lose her anyway.
Any advice?
- A very confused fresher.
